ould AOE the entire village?<br>3. Will the Weeping Wand still improve my channeling at level 53?<br><br>Thanks in advance<br> <p>Oanka Lorekeeper/Lydell Lorekeeper <BR>Sacred Guardians <BR>Fennin Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=yiliamar>Yiliamar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/27/01 10:23:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=354.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Moral Issue with the Weeping Wand</span><hr size=1> 1) Not that I've ever heard.<br>2) Because they are annoying? (Sorry, my ranger waited 4 hours for the princess to spawn.  Damn bells drove me nuts.)<br>3) I've not noticed any improvement in channelling while holding my WW.<br><br>Just kill them.  You won't feel so bad when you have to keep AEing the village waiting for the blasted silk to drop. (Took about 2 hours for me and 2 mages to get my silk.)<br> <p>Yours in flames,</br>Yiliamar Darkember</br>Worshiper of Solusek Ro</br>Quellious Server</br>www.angelfire.com/games2/NNB/</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=british>British</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/27/01 11:03:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=354.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Moral Issue with the Weeping Wand</span><hr size=1> &gt;2. Is there a good reason why I should AOE the entire <br>&gt;village?<br><br>Yes, because they make a funny noise when they die.  I've only killed Faeries individually - I would imagine hearing several &quot;Aaaaiieeeee!!!!&quot;s in unison would be hysterical.<br><br>I can also tell you that these creatures are anything BUT peaceful and kind.  They always attack me whenever I am sitting at the GFay spires...  Wretched little things...<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udaeanorendarion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daeanor Endarion</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.monmouth.com/~dhawthorne/everqst/picon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/2/01 4:49:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=354.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.monmouth.com/~dhawthorne/everqst/ppic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Moral Issue with the Weeping Wand</span><hr size=1> I will confirm, AE'ing the entire village makes a really interesting squeal. I have killed hundreds of the little bugs (remember that lame movie Labyrinth, with David Bowie? Dorf in the beginning was killin' fairies with pesticide spray <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) for various quests, and am still only dubious. If it's any consolation, many &quot;good&quot; race quests want them dead. <p><table><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#cc0000 strength=1)><font size=2 color=#ffff00 face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Daeanor Endarion of the Rathe</font></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulummanaburn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LumManaburn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/2/01 5:34:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=354.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Moral Issue with the Weeping Wand</span><hr size=1> When I was doing the quest and needed the silk (oh soo many levels ago) the faerie guards were blue to us. A friend and I decided to stay there since we were getting exp and they drop Fine Steel which we could sell at the ranger camp. <br><br>The faerie dust is needed for SK darkforge boots and Paly Ro armour. I remember selling the dust for 10p each back then. Between the dust, cash and FS it was a profitable afternoon. <br> <p><center>Luminea Manaburn <BR>52 Channeler<BR>Drunks of Tunare <BR><img border="0" src="http://home.mindspring.com/~pcadam/_uimages/vox2.gif" width="200" height="120"><BR></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uadoryn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adoryn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/13/01 11:26:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=354.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://adoryn.com/junk/icon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Moral Issue with the Weeping Wand</span><hr size=1> Taking bad faction from faeries doesn't interfere with anything else and they have several quest item drops. Even if you are worried, it takes a long time to become KOS. I've killed tons of faeries and I'm still apprehensive. <br><br>On occassion I've seen druids using harmony to kill faerie guards for experience, perhaps they'll let you loot the silk from their kills if you still refuse to harm the faeries. <p><center><table border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=2><tr><td align=center><font face=Verdana size=2><b>*Adoryn*</b></td></tr><tr><td align=center> <font face=Verdana size=1>Bristlebane || 52 Wizardess || Windwalkers</td></tr></table></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/17/01 2:32:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=354.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.docsmooth.com/images/me.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Moral Issue with the Weeping Wand</span><hr size=1> A bit up someone said they've noticed no difference with the WW up - I'd like to differ.  Before the WW, if a HG hit me, I'd be screwed.  Unless I got DANG lucky to get a yonder off, I was dead.  now, I can actually ROOT them and back off, so that I can fight more.  And yes, i'm normally fighting 'em w/ much higher groups for the pp.  Heck, I dodged an HG the other day.  His hands are as big as my body, andhe missed. heeh <p><br>Aniar Orrenson<br>Wizard of the 29th Season<br>High Councilman of the Nightwatch of Norrath<br>"You look up overkill in the dictionary and there's a picture of Aniar lol" Lotta on Saryrn</p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showPrevMessage?topicID=354.topi